==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boxhaul
<hw>Box"haul`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Boxhauled</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To put (a vessel) on the other tack by veering
her short round on her heel; -- so called from the circumstance of
bracing the head yards abox (i. e., sharp aback, on the wind).</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boxhauling</ent>⟦br⟧
